 laid down the foundations for the eventual emergence of their full-fledged auteurism.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0https://www.aup.nl/en/publish/open-access  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Feb 2021) 0aAuteur theory (Motion pictures). 0aMotion pictures. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAUP eBook Package 2016-2018z978311066731808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press eBook Package 2018z978311060672040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048537037zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048537037zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9789048537037.jpg  a978-3-11-060672-0 Amsterdam University Press eBook Package 2018b2018  a978-3-11-066731-8 AUP eBook Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA